info.name: gerbolyze
info.summary: A high-resolution image-to-PCB converter. Gerbolyze reads and vectorizes black-and-white raster images, then plots the vectorized image into an existing gerber file while avoiding existing features such as text or holes.

info.author: jaseg
classifiers: License :: OSI Approved :: GNU Affero General Public License v3 or later (AGPLv3+)
info.name: gerbolyze
info.summary: A high-resolution image-to-PCB converter. Gerbolyze plots SVG, PNG and JPG onto existing gerber files. It handles almost the full SVG spec and deals with text, path outlines, patterns, arbitrary paths with self-intersections and holes, etc. fully automatically. It can vectorize raster images both by contour tracing and by grayscale dithering. All processing is done at the vector level without intermediate conversions to raster images accurately preserving the input.
